title: pain
subtitle: stuff
content: Some notes to myself. Foreign investments keeps the dollar stronger. US has lost it's triple A credit rating. The promise of AI as the next wave of innovation and a steady job market keeps foreign and domestic inflows. The dollar can't depreciate yet but it's overvalued.  Tariffs seemingly tries to combat this issue. If the dollar depricates --> less purchasing power and thus imports become more expensive and our exports become more cheaper.
